name: Underwood Memorial Baptist Church
directions: Open Sunday Mornings- Enter through the main church doors, up one flight of stairs and turn right. For wheelchair accesibility, enter the glass elevator vestibule, take elevator up one stop and exit elevator to the left. Restroom has "All Gender Restroom" sign on door. Gendered multi-stall restrooms are located downstairs.
comment: Open Sunday mornings. Yes, it's a church- which may throw you- but this is a welcoming and affirming church which means that all people are welcome just as they are.

name: Humane Society of Washington County
directions:
Two sets - 

1. Intake/Lost & Found side - go in and turn left. Two bathrooms on the right side near the glass doors.
2. In the Adoptions lobby. Turn right almost immediately, after the vending machine. Two bathrooms.
comment: If you don't feel comfortable just walking in, you can ask for KP during the week, and I'll come out & pretend like we have an appointment. (I do occasionally have meetings, but I'll do my best)

name: Mitzpah AMC Hut
directions: Located at the AMC Mizpah Spring Hut.  Park at the Crawford Notch trail head in Bretton  Woods, NH and follow the Crawford Path for 1.5 miles.  Take the Mizpah Cutoff trail for a direct route to the hut and restroom.
comment: An alternate route with amazing views is to take the Crawford Notch trail and summit Mt. Pierce, a NH “4000 footer” mountain, then follow the Webster trail to the hut and return down via the Mizpah Cutoff trail.

name: Wildlife Science Center
directions: The Wildlife Science Center has two gender neutral restrooms located in the hallway of the main education building.
comment: The Wildlife Science Center must be open to the public for the restrooms to be accessible. Check their hours online.

name: University of Hertfordshire de Havilland Campus
directions: Ground Floor of the Law Court Building on the De Havilland Campus, near Cafe Moot.
comment: There are gender neutral toilets across both university campuses following a successful pilot, however this is the only one that I have personally used.  The campus is obviously a little bit out of the way but this information may be useful to people visiting the site.  The university has published trans guidance/policy.

comment: This is at Pinetree Community Centre

name: Fools Gold NYC
directions: Gender neutral bathroom is located towards the rear of the bar and has historically been adorned with "Everybody Poops" artwork.  The bar has noted that the door was recently replaced due to a broken lock, but that they will be having it repainted shortly.
comment: The bar has confirmed that they are "a trans-friendly location and totally safe bathroom for anyone, especially with the trans/gender non-conforming community."

name: Hollywood Theatre

comment: During movie times-all restrooms are 'general seating'!
